      <ExplanationTxt>THE WINDERMERE VOLUNTEER FIRE DEPARTMENT INADVERTENTLY FAILED TO FILE AN EXTENSION FOR TAX YEAR 2019. THE FIRE DEPARTMENT'S TREASURER AND BUSINESS MANAGER BOTH RESIGNED IN 2019 AND MOVED OUT OF STATE. ALSO, THE BOARD WAS UNABLE TO MEET DUE TO COVID 19 RESTRICTIONS AND QUARANTINE. WE RESPECTFULLY REQUEST THAT PENALTIES ASSOCIATED WITH LATE FILING BE WAIVED DUE TO THESE EXTENUATING CIRCUMSTANCES. THANK YOU FOR YOUR CONSIDERATION.</ExplanationTxt>
